<p>IVC Script = indigenous in character&nbsp;</p>
<p>by Ancient tamil speaking people&nbsp;</p>
<p>script clearly shows identity with existing Tamil Script.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Evidences for linguistic and cultural similarity</h3>
<ol>
<li>certain letter in tamil are taken from indus valley&nbsp;</li>
<li>in IVC script, consonants do not have dots over them. same letters in tolkapiyyam are said to have dots.</li>
<li>letters in tamil indicate rituals of burning the dead. Similar practices are seen in IVC</li></ol>
<h3>mauryas and sangam literature</h3>
<ol>
<li>Mauryas invaded southern region. (Bindusar 297 - 273 BC)</li>
<li>Eight anthologies of sangam age = refer mauryan invasion. Why mauryan invasion important = first such incident where north and south boundaries united.</li></ol>
